		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><s>I have idea to make a new hardware related to NES/Famicom. It has USB to connect to a computer &#40;or other unit that you can connect USB devices to&#41;, both 60-pin and 72-pin slot, and a built-in filesystem. It could also have other kind of connections other than USB if needed.<br /><br />Either have a read-only jumper inside the unit &#40;as well as jumper to disable filesystem and jumper to disablet he cartridges&#41;, or a way to access the filesystem reprogrammable ROM when the unit is open.<br /><br />And then the device will also act as connection between cartridge and computer so that the computer program can emulate the interface to play game &#40;or copy the cartridge data, or backup save files, or testing mappers, or whatever&#41;.</s>

		

