		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I started making something like this years ago (2004?), search the forums for "copycart".  It's basically a USB-to-5V GPIO converter, with the gpio hooked up to a 72 pin connector.  I had PCB's made, but never bothered to solder down the electronics or write the software for it.  The real dealbreaker for me was the 72 pin connector, finding one of those is impossible.

		

